oc:kn_0a7434af a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, when presenting any financial output" ;
    oc:directiveContent "This skill does not provide financial advice. All statements should be reviewed by qualified financial professionals before use in reporting or filings." ;
    oc:hasRationale "AI-generated financial statements may contain errors that could have regulatory or legal consequences if relied upon without professional review" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_1f72ca10 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating cash flow statements under GAAP (ASC 230 / IAS 7)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For the cash flow statement, use the indirect method (start with net income, adjust for non-cash items). Disclose interest paid and income taxes paid. Disclose non-cash investing and financing activities separately." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The indirect method is the most common and widely understood format; required disclosures ensure compliance" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4232efd8 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When investigating material variances" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Variance decomposition: break each material variance into volume/quantity effect, rate/price effect, mix effect, new/discontinued items, one-time/non-recurring items, timing effect, and currency effect." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Decomposition reveals the true business drivers behind a variance, enabling targeted action rather than surface-level explanations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_584f1f1a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before generating financial statements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Requires either connected ERP/data warehouse for automatic data pull, or user-provided trial balance data, spreadsheet upload, or income statement data." .

oc:kn_5877e45e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When executing the full financial statement generation workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Gather financial data (trial balance, comparison periods, account hierarchy) from ERP/data warehouse or user input. 2. Generate income statement in multi-column format with current, prior, variance ($/%), budget, and budget variance columns. 3. Calculate variance decomposition for material variances. 4. Produce key metrics summary (margins, growth rates, tax rate). 5. Compile material variance summary table with direction, drivers, and required actions. 6. Deliver formatted output with follow-up questions." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_6780854d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before finalizing any period-end financial statements" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Period-end adjustments checklist: (1) Accruals for incurred but unpaid expenses, (2) Deferral adjustments for prepaid expenses and deferred revenue, (3) Depreciation/amortization booking, (4) Bad debt provision based on aging analysis, (5) Inventory write-downs, (6) FX revaluation of monetary items, (7) Tax provision, (8) Fair value adjustments." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing period-end adjustments is a leading cause of financial statement restatements" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_74be3ec4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting the income statement output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """INCOME STATEMENT columns: Current Period | Prior Period | Variance ($) | Variance (%) | Budget Amount | Budget Var ($)
Sections: REVENUE → COST OF REVENUE → GROSS PROFIT (with margin %) → OPERATING EXPENSES (R&D, S&M, G&A) → OPERATING INCOME (with margin %) → OTHER INCOME/EXPENSE → INCOME BEFORE TAXES → NET INCOME (with margin %)

KEY METRICS: Revenue growth, Gross margin, Operating margin, Net margin, OpEx % of revenue, Effective tax rate — with period-over-period change in percentage points.""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "Budget Amount",
        "Budget Var ($)",
        "Current Period",
        "Prior Period",
        "Variance ($)",
        "Variance (%)" .

oc:kn_bbb613b5 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating income statements under GAAP (ASC 220 / IAS 1)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classify expenses by function (COGS, R&D, S&M, G&A) for US companies; if classified by function, disclose depreciation, amortization, and employee benefit costs by nature in the notes. Extraordinary items are prohibited under both US GAAP and IFRS." ;
    oc:hasRationale "GAAP presentation standards require consistent classification and prohibit extraordinary items to ensure comparability" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c630c677 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When determining which variances require investigation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use scaled materiality thresholds: >$10M line items flag at $500K/5%, $1M-$10M at $100K/10%, <$1M at $50K/15%. Combine dollar and percentage thresholds—flag if either is exceeded." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Fixed thresholds miss material percentage moves on small accounts or immaterial dollar moves on large accounts" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f654570d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When generating balance sheets under GAAP (ASC 210 / IAS 1)" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Distinguish current vs non-current assets and liabilities. Present assets in order of liquidity (most liquid first). Show AR net of allowance for credit losses (ASC 326), PPE net of accumulated depreciation, and recognize right-of-use assets and lease liabilities (ASC 842). Goodwill is not amortized—tested for impairment annually (ASC 350)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Balance sheet classification errors are common audit findings and affect financial ratio calculations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

